%U A395259 7,3,8,3,2,5,9,4,1,2,5,3,8,6,0,6,3,1,6,0
%N A395259 Decimal expansion of the number defined by the continued fraction 1/(r+1/(r+1/(r + ...))), where r is the bronze ratio (A098316).
%C A395259 Repeat s = s + (3+sqrt(13))/2; s=1/s. The initial value of s is irrelevant, as long as s != -(3+sqrt(13))/2.
%C A395259 An algebraic integer.
%C A395259 In general, for the metallic number M = [N; N, N, N, ...], the number defined by the continued fraction [0; M, M, M, ...] is the smallest positive real root of x^4 + N*x^3 - 3*x^2 - N*x + 1 = 0.
%H A395259 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metallic_mean">Metallic mean</a>
%H A395259 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A395259 Equals [0; A098316, A098316, A098316, ...].
%F A395259 Equals (sqrt(38+6*sqrt(13))-3-sqrt(13))/4.
%F A395259 Equals 1/A189964.
%F A395259 Equals A189964 - A098316.
%F A395259 Smallest positive real root of x^4 + 3*x^3 - 3*x^2 - 3*x + 1 = 0.
%e A395259 0.2791773129798557305129290621857967137862432614...
%t A395259 RealDigits[(Sqrt[38+6*Sqrt[13]]-3-Sqrt[13])/4,10,88][[1]] (* _Stefano Spezia_, Apr 17 2026 *)
%o A395259 (PARI) (sqrt(38+6*sqrt(13))-3-sqrt(13))/4
%o A395259 (PARI) polrootsreal(Pol([1, 3, -3, -3, 1]))[3]
%Y A395259 Cf. A098316, A189964.
%Y A395259 Similar constants defined by continued fractions: A010527 (real part for r=i), A086773 (r=Pi), A086774 (r=exp(1)), A086775 (r=(1+sqrt(5))/2), A101263 (r=sqrt(2)), A188485-1 (r=1/2), A340616 (r=2*sqrt(2)), A394765 (r=1+sqrt(2)).
